            "description": "Art + Food + Brainstem touch\nEatArt expericnce by Takako Hamano and Uno Fujisawa\n\nWe believe that deeper senses in experiencing everyday happenings can make our life and mother earth a better place.In EatArt Salon you can experience art, foodart and brainstem touch* with Japanese essence to open up five senses. While you gain a special combination of relaxation, creative inspirations, health input and place to share experiences with others, you contribute to make a forest in Japan a little more green.\n\nWe have our regular sessions at LOSDOK project space in Amsterdam and pop ups in other locations.\n\n* Brainstem touch is a Japanese dry head spa, a brand new offer in NL,\nwhich relaxes your body & mind and activates your five senses.",
